Class AscendinglyOrderedList<T extends KeyedItem<KT>,KT extends java.lang.Comparable<? super KT>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • AscendinglyOrderedList<T,KT>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of items held in this collection
    KT - the type of each item's search key

    public class AscendinglyOrderedList<T extends KeyedItem<KT>,KT extends java.lang.Comparable<? super KT>>
extends java.lang.Object
    A sorted list with all of its elements in ascending order. The items in this list are ordered based on their search keys. An ArrayBasedList is used to hold all of the items in this collection. Items can retrieved and removed using their search keys or by index. Adding items can only be done based on their search keys. This ensures all items are always in sorted order.
